snippet: A wave of demonstrations against King Abdullah II set off by an increase in fuel prices appeared to reach its peak on Friday as thousands of protesters gathered in Amman to call for the monarch’s ouster.
abstract: Wave of demonstrations against Jordan's King Abdullah II set off by an increase in fuel prices appears to reach its peak as thousands of protesters gathered in Amman to call for the monarch’s ouster.
lead_paragraph: A wave of demonstrations against King Abdullah II set off by an increase in fuel prices appeared to reach its peak on Friday as thousands of protesters gathered in Amman to call for the monarch’s ouster.
